10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note: </strong><em>Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Wednesday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Covid and insider trading (1)</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMTMvZnJhdWQtaXMtbm8tZnVuLXdpdGhvdXQtZnJpZW5kcz9=
jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzAzMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bm=
V3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MDMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB9b41d432" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked</a> a few <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMTYvdHJhZGVycy1kby1sZXNzLWNyaW1=
lLWF0LWhvbWU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcwMzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG=
1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzAzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0d=
WZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc2341c44" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  times</a> about the effect=
 of working from home on financial crime. You could imagine it going either=
 way: Being out of the office might cause you to do more crime, because you=
 are less closely observed by bosses and compliance, or more crime, because=
 you are not around peer pressure to do crime. Empirically, though,=C2=A0th=
e answer seems to be =E2=80=9Cless crime.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That said, there is one classic form of financ=
ial crime that I=C2=A0<em>think=C2=A0</em>would have to be increased by wor=
k-from-home? That form of financial crime is =E2=80=9Clooking at your girlf=
riend=E2=80=99s computer to see what high-stakes deals she is working on,<a=
 class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpa=
rent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> and then insider trading on them.=E2=80=9D People love that one. If yo=
ur girlfriend mostly works from her law firm=E2=80=99s or investment bank=
=E2=80=99s office, but logs in at night=C2=A0or does weekend conference cal=
ls on live deals, you might pick up some information to trade on, though sh=
e might remember to use code names when you=E2=80=99re in earshot and lock =
her computer when she steps away. But if she works from home all day every =
day in your one-bedroom apartment, you are just far more likely=C2=A0to kno=
w what she is working on. And if you are inclined to trade on it, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0xMjQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB2b6b88f2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> you will</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Thursd=
ay] announced insider trading charges against Jordan Meadow, a registered r=
epresentative for a New York-based broker-dealer, and Steven Teixeira, the =
Chief Compliance Officer of an international payment processing company, in=
 connection with their trading based on material nonpublic information that=
 Teixeira obtained from his girlfriend=E2=80=99s laptop while she was worki=
ng at home during the COVID-19 pandemic.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s complaint alleges that Teixe=
ira accessed nonpublic information on possible upcoming mergers and acquisi=
tions of public companies from the laptop of his girlfriend, who was employ=
ed at a prominent New York-based investment bank. As alleged, Teixeira then=
 used the information to purchase call options on several issuers ahead of =
the announcement of the deals and tipped the information to his friends, in=
cluding Meadow, so that they could trade as well. The scheme allegedly gene=
rated illicit profits of approximately $28,600 for Teixeira, while Meadow m=
ade more than $730,000. Additionally, according to the complaint, Meadow re=
commended trades to his brokerage customers based on the material nonpublic=
 information from Teixeira, resulting in millions of dollars in profits for=
 them and hundreds of thousands of dollars in commissions for Meadow.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9COur complaint alleges brazen betrayal=
s of trust by Teixeira, who misappropriated information from his girlfriend=
=E2=80=99s laptop to make a quick buck, and by industry-veteran Meadow, who=
 was all too eager to use the information to line his pockets,=E2=80=9D sai=
d Scott Thompson, the Associate Regional Director of the SEC=E2=80=99s Phil=
adelphia Regional Office. =E2=80=9CWe will continue to pursue and prosecute=
 insider trading where appropriate to hold people accountable for their act=
ions.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are also <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3Yvd=
XNhby1zZG55L3ByL3VzLWF0dG9ybmV5LWFubm91bmNlcy1jaGFyZ2VzLWZvdXItc2VwYXJhdGUt=
aW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5nLWNhc2VzLWFnYWluc3QtMTA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3b1e10=
de" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> criminal charges</a>. Always the compliance officers, always =
the call options. The girlfriend was an executive assistant at the investme=
nt bank (reportedly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jMtMDYtMjkvYnJva2VyLWNoYXJnZWQtb3Zlci1pbnNpZGUtZGF0YS1zdG9sZW4tZnJvbS1iYW5r=
LXdvcmtlci1zLWxhcHRvcD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzAzMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWV=
tYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MDMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW=
1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB876692dd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Morgan Stanley</=
a>), <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31975621.2574=
07/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9jb21wLXBy=
MjAyMy0xMjQucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB06175c76" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> where she</a> =
=E2=80=9Cwas responsible for, among other things, scheduling meetings of th=
e Investment Bank=E2=80=99s valuation and fairness=C2=A0committees concerni=
ng potential transactions involving the Investment Bank=E2=80=99s clients=
=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Deal teams working on transactions=
 provided the Executive Assistant with scheduling request forms for valuati=
on and fairness committee meetings. These forms included the names of the c=
ompanies participating in, and the material terms relating to, the proposed=
 deals. The Executive Assistant created and sent calendar invitations for t=
he meetings, attaching the scheduling request forms to the invitations.=C2=
=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Teixeira accessed the Executive As=
sistant=E2=80=99s laptop while she was away=E2=80=94either out of the room =
or away from the apartment entirely. Using his access, Teixeira reviewed th=
e Executive Assistant=E2=80=99s Outlook application to find valuation and f=
airness committee meetings relating to mergers and acquisitions of public c=
ompanies.=C2=A0He then reviewed the attachment=C2=A0containing the party na=
mes and material terms of potential transactions involving the Investment B=
ank=E2=80=99s clients.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure, right, of course. The executive assistan=
t for the fairness committee is far more useful, for insider trading, than =
a high-powered investment banker would be: The banker sees mostly her own d=
eals; the committee assistant sees just enough information on every deal.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also there is a great information-security det=
ail here.=C2=A0The bank was careful about remote access to data, to prevent=
 exactly this sort of thing:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Investment Bank=E2=80=99s onli=
ne portal for employees working remotely locked automatically after a perio=
d of inactivity. The system could detect that an employee was not typing or=
 moving their mouse, for example, and would require the employee to log in =
again to access the Investment Bank=E2=80=99s files.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This security system had a downside, though, w=
hich is that it is=C2=A0<em>annoying</em>. Nobody wants to be logged out of=
 their remote work every time they go to the bathroom. So:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Teixeira provided the Executive As=
sistant with a device that moved the Executive Assistant=E2=80=99s mouse wh=
ile she was away from her computer. This device simulated user activity and=
 prevented the Investment Bank=E2=80=99s online portal from detecting that =
the Executive Assistant was away from her computer, which would otherwise c=
ause the system to lock and require the Executive Assistant to log in to ac=
cess the Investment Bank=E2=80=99s files.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So she could go to the bathroom without having=
 to log back in, and also he could steal her bank=E2=80=99s information and=
 insider trade on it. The trick with information security is that you have =
to make your security measures strong enough to defeat criminals, but not s=
o strong that they annoy your employees into disabling them.=C2=A0</p>
