<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have a thesis that artificial intellige=
nce will reshape the world and revolutionize every industry, how should you=
 invest? Some options:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Invest in AI companies, companies tha=
t are working to develop AI technology. Presumably they=E2=80=99ll find a w=
ay to make money with it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Invest i=
n chip companies, betting that the rise of AI will lead to rising demand fo=
r powerful microchips. A sell-shovels-in-a-gold-rush strategy.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Invest in  pizza delivery startups, betting th=
at the rise of AI will create new possibilities for increased efficiency of=
 pizza delivery, and that your portfolio of pizza-delivery startups will ca=
pture the upside. I dunno, man.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today the Wall Street Journal has a <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9oZS1zcGVudC0xNDAtYmlsbGlvbi1vbi1haS13aXRoLWxpdHR=
sZS10by1zaG93LW5vdy1oZS1pcy10cnlpbmctYWdhaW4tZGJjY2ExNz9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3=
Mx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBefc1bb13" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">funny and rather cruel story<=
/a> about how SoftBank Group went all-in on artificial intelligence in 2018=
, invested $140 billion in the theme, and somehow =E2=80=A6=C2=A0missed it =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0entirely?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe are not just recklessly making inv=
estments,=E2=80=9D [SoftBank CEO Masayoshi] Son told investors in 2018. =E2=
=80=9CWe are focusing on one theme, which is AI.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Despite the unprecedented spending spree that =
Son in 2020 said would make SoftBank =E2=80=9Cthe investment company for th=
e AI revolution,=E2=80=9D one of the world=E2=80=99s most prolific tech inv=
estors has missed out on the frenzy in generative AI, the red-hot subsector=
 in which products such as ChatGPT learn from huge datasets to create uniqu=
e text or images.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Tokyo-based conglomerate has invested in j=
ust one of the 26 generative AI startups valued at more than $1 billion, ac=
cording to PitchBook. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0SoftBank missed out on huge gains at A=
I-focused chip maker Nvidia: The Tokyo-based investor put around $4 billion=
 into the company in 2017, only to sell its shares in 2019. Nvidia stock is=
 up about 10 times since.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is possible that the problem is that Son wa=
s=C2=A0<em>too </em>optimistic about AI:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In quirky investor presentations that featured=
 diagrams with dinosaurs and steam engines, the SoftBank CEO said AI would =
=E2=80=9Credefine all industries=E2=80=9D and usher in a powerful new wave =
of the information revolution that began with computers=E2=80=94language si=
milar to that many CEOs have begun using in recent months. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During the years that SoftBank was investing, =
it generally avoided companies focused specifically on developing AI techno=
logy. Instead, it poured money into companies that Son said were leveraging=
 AI and would benefit from its growth. For example, it put billions of doll=
ars into numerous self-driving car tech companies, which tend to use AI to =
help learn how humans drive and react to objects on the road. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Son told investors that AI would power huge ex=
pansions at numerous companies where, years later, the benefits are unclear=
 or nonexistent. In 2018, he highlighted AI at real-estate agency Compass, =
now-bankrupt construction company Katerra, and office-rental company WeWork=
, which he said would use AI to analyze how people communicate and then sel=
l them products.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Intuitively a thesis like =E2=80=9CAI will red=
efine all industries=E2=80=9D gets expressed by=C2=A0<em>investing in all i=
ndustries</em>, picking the companies in each industry that will use AI the=
 best, not investing in generative-AI developers. If you go around saying i=
n public =E2=80=9Cwe think that AI will transform every industry and we pla=
n to invest absolute gobs of money along those lines,=E2=80=9D then perhaps=
 someone building a generative-AI company will come to you and ask you for =
some of that money.=C2=A0But=C2=A0<em>definitely=C2=A0</em>people who are b=
uilding real-estate agencies or construction companies or office-rental com=
panies or <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31975621=
.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDI=
tMTQvcm9ib3QtcGl6emEtdHJ1Y2tzLWhpdC1zb21lLWJ1bXBzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyM19NT0=
5FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtP=
TIzMDcwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2cfdbe83=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">pizza-delivery companies</a> will say =E2=80=9Chuh, the guy with =
all the money wants to invest in AI transforming every industry, let=E2=80=
=99s get some of that money,=E2=80=9D and they will add slides to their dec=
ks like =E2=80=9CHow We Will Use AI To Transform Pizza Delivery=E2=80=9D wi=
th clip art of a robot and a pizza,=C2=A0and your eyes will light up when y=
ou see that slide and you will say =E2=80=9Csee=C2=A0<em>this=C2=A0</em>is =
what I am talking=C2=A0about, AI is gonna transform all the industries, her=
e=E2=80=99s $375 million.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the way the bull case here is that he was j=
ust early, and SoftBank really did manage to pick all the companies that wi=
ll do the best job of deploying AI to redefine their industries, and in 10 =
years all of us will work out of WeWorks because WeWork is uniquely good at=
 using AI models to, you know, adjust the air conditioning and dynamically =
price desk space and whatever. The real upshot of the computer revolution i=
s that every company became a tech company, and I suppose the real upshot o=
f the AI revolution=C2=A0might be that every company becomes an AI company,=
 and some will get there faster than others. I don=E2=80=99t have any=C2=A0=
<em>reason=C2=A0</em>to think that Son did pick all the right winners, but =
it is perhaps too early to tell.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/31975621.257407/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2x=
lcy9jcnlwdG8tbWluZXJzLXNlZWstYS1uZXctbGlmZS1pbi1haS1ib29tLWFmdGVyLWFuLWltcG=
