524a319a23cBed5f8efc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">industries getting transformed by AI</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The boom in demand for high-end chips powering=
 the rise of artificial intelligence has given new life to some of the surv=
ivors of the last tech-hype cycle: cryptocurrency miners.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During the crypto upsurge, Satoshi Spain sold =
and leased out hundreds of souped-up computers=E2=80=94known as mining rigs=
=E2=80=94equipped with powerful graphics chips. Then, as many of them sat i=
dle starting last year because of the decline of mining currencies, the Spa=
nish company began helping its customers retool the machines for AI.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today, Satoshi Spain=E2=80=99s machines are ha=
ndling AI workloads for startups, universities and individual developers in=
 Europe.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CYou can still make money from your mi=
ning rig,=E2=80=9D Satoshi Spain founder Alejandro Ib=C3=A1=C3=B1ez de Pedr=
o said. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s mining 2.0.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It would be very funny if, completely by accid=
ent,=C2=A0the big winners from the AI boom were crypto miners.</p>
